Method Detail

run

public void run()
Executes the call as specified during the construction of this object. After the call completes, done is set to true and all threads waiting on this Executor are awoken. The thread can be interrupted (via Thread.interrupt()) in case of a timeout; if this happens, the call is aborted.

Specified by:
run in interface java.lang.Runnable
